40|$|We {{study the}} {{low-energy}} effective theory of spinor condensate <b>ferromagnets</b> for the superfluid velocity and magnetization degrees of freedom. This effective theory describes {{the competition between}} spin stiffness and a long-ranged interaction between skyrmions, topological objects familiar from the theory of ordinary <b>ferromagnets.</b> We find exact solutions to the non-linear equations of motion describing neutral configurations of skyrmions and anti-skyrmions. These analytical solutions provide a simple physical picture for the origin of crystalline magnetic order in spinor condensate <b>ferromagnets</b> with dipolar interactions. We also point out the connections to effective theories for quantum Hall <b>ferromagnets.</b> Comment: 13 pages, 7 figure...|$|R
