40|$|We study {{theoretically}} {{the spin}} transfer {{effect on a}} domain wall in disordered weak <b>ferromagnets.</b> We have identified the adiabatic condition for the disordered case as λ≫λ_ D≡√(ħ D/), where D and are the diffusion constant and the spin splitting energy due to the s-d type exchange interaction, respectively, {{and found out that}} perfect spin-transfer effect occurs even in weak <b>ferromagnets</b> as long as this condition is satisfied. The effective β term arising from the force turns out to govern the wall dynamics, and therefore, the wall motion can be as efficient as in strong <b>ferromagnets</b> even if is small...|$|R
